rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that stores information about information technology certifications, viz. formal confirmations that a person has a certain level of ability with respect to a particular hardware/software product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Certification

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that provides a standard descriptor for the certification, e.g. "Amazon Web Services Certified Solutions Architect - Associate".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Certificate

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date, if any, when the certification expires.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Expires

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date when the certification was given to the person holding it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Granted

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the organization that conferred the certification.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the product, viz. a particular family/version of software/hardware, with respect to which the given person has the certification.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Product

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains any computing service that is made available over the Internet.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cloud Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type collecting the data on the way in which a given piece of software allows code to be generated automatically using templates or class diagrams.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Code Generation Supported

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.code_generation_supported relationship to the mso:common.diagram_type the tool can use to generate code.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Diagram Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.code_generation_supported relationship to the mso:computer.programming_language that code can be generated into given a diagram type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Programming Languages

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all compression/decompression formats. These are the standards that regulate the way the data is stored in order to encode or decode a digital data stream. A device or software program that preforms this encoding or decoding is called a codec.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Compression/Decompression Format

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all computers. Computers are the set of general purpose devices that can be programmed to carry out a set of arithmetic or logical operations. By this definition, computers would include laptops, smartphones, tablets, and mainframes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.computer to the types of connections to import and export data on instances of the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Connectivity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a computer to the date when manufacturing of the computer stopped.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Discontinued

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.computer to the type of display that accompanies the device. Some types of mso:computer.computer will have display options as a peripheral, like most desktop machines, and others, like smartphone, will include a display means as part of the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Display

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a given computer to software that allows the functions of another computer system to be replicated on the given computer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Emulators

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.computer to the type of graphics processing unit the computer uses.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Graphical Processing Unit

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer to a submodel of the computer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Includes Models

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date when this computer was first made available to the general public
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Introduced

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer to one of the most important people involved in the design the computer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Key Designers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer to the company reponsible for the fabrication of the computer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Manufacturer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.computer to the compatible network protocols for instances of the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Networking

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer to a supermodel of the computer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Parent Model

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer to a peripheral (e.g. monitor, keyboard or memory device) that is compatible with the computer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Peripherals

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer to a processor that is a component of the computer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Processor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer to the maximum number of processors supported by the computer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Processor Scalability

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computing device to the number of slots in the device for SIM (Subscriber Identity Module) cards.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: SIM Card Slots

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computing device to the type of SIM (Subscriber Identity Module) cards, e.g. nano or micro, used by the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: SIM Card Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.computer to the read and write random access memory available to the end user on the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Storage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that renders computer output on a screen.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Monitor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer monitor to the resolution that the monitor has within the context of a particular game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: In-game Resolution

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer monitor to the number of times per second that the screen of the monitor is redrawn.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Refresh Rate

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Indicates whether or not the computer monitor incorporates thin film transistor technology. This technology uses a separate transistor for each pixel, which means that the display of the monitor can be redrawn very quickly.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Thin-film Transistor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A person who specializes in computer science, viz. the study of the theoretical foundations of computing machinery.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Scientist

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of computing standards. These are the technical standards for hardware and software that allow for interoperability between software, systems, platforms, and devices.
Property relating an mso:computer.computer_standard to the date of the latest version.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Latest Version

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all computer stores. These are the stores specializing in computers and other similar electronics for sale.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The environment within which software is designed to run. This may include hardware, operating system, supporting software, and runtime libraries.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computing Platform

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computing platform to a file format that is compatible with the platform.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: File Formats Supported

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A legal document that specifies how and by whom the given content can be used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Content License

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all data catalogs. These are collections of datasets that are presented as a unified whole.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Data Catalog

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.data_catalog to one of its mso:computer.datasets.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dataset

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all sets of data. A dataset can, for example, refer to the contents of a database table or any other set of structured information over a common topic.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Data Set

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.dataset to the mso:computer.data_catalog the dataset is a part of.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Catalog

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.dataset to the date(s) applied to the dataset. For example, for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.dataset to the mso:location.location the dataset is applicable to. For example, for a dataset of New York weather, the state of New York.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A person who has credit for the design of a computing device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Designer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer designer to one of the computers that he or she designed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computers Designed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A personal computer that has various external components, e.g. a keyboard, mouse, and monitor, and is designed to be used on a desk.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Desktop Computer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of disc labelling technologies like DiscT@2 and LabelFlash.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Disc Labelling Technology

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Software that allows the functions of a given computer system to be replicated in another computer system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Emulator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an emulator to a computer system that the emulator emulates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Emulated Computer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an emulator to a specific peripheral that the emulator emulates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Emulated Peripheral

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an emulator to a class of peripherals that the emulator emulates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Emulated Peripheral Classes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A standard way that information is encoded for storage in a computer file, e.g. PDF or DOC.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: File Format

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a file format to a metafile format that includes it. For example, Ogg is a container format for Vorbis, Theora, Opus, FLAC, Dirac, and others.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Container Format

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a metafile file format to a file format that it includes. For example, Vorbis, Theora, Opus, FLAC, Dirac, and others are included in the metafile format Ogg.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Contained Format

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a file format to the date that the format was first introduced.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Creation Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a file format to another file format, when the first extends the second. For example, .DOCX is an extension of the .DOC format. An extension may or may not be backwards compatible with the original format.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Extended File Format

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a file format to another file format which extends it. For example, .DOCX is an extension of the .DOC format. An extension may or may not be backwards compatible with the original format.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Extending File Format

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a file format to the identifier for the file format. For example, ".pdf" is the identifier for the Portable Document Format.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Extension

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a file format to the film format genre that it exemplifies, e.g. ".DOC" and word processor.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Genre

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a file format to the person, company or organization that is responsible for creating the file format.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Format Creator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An alphanumeric string that is included inside a file and uniquely identifies the format of the file.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Magic Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a file format to a computer program that is capable of performing operations on the file format.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Input

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a file format to a computing platform which is compatible with the file format.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Platforms

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a file format to a computer program that is capable of creating files with the given file format.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Output

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A standard classifier for the kind of file format or the kind of software that produces the file format, e.g. word processor or spreadsheet.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: File Format Genre

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a file format genre to a film format that is an example of this genre, e.g. ".DOC" and word processor.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: File Formats

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A small, non-volatile, and reprogrammable electronic data storage device that be plugged into a USB port of the given device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flash Drive

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all graphics processing units. These specialized circuits are responsible for manipulation of memory to create the images for display.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Graphical Processing Unit

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A storage device consisting of a read/write mechanism and one or more hard disks.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hard Drive

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.hard_drive to the size of its buffer. The buffer is temporary memory storage used when data is being moved from one place to another.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Buffer Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The amount of data, in Bytes, that can be stored on the given hard drive.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hard Drive Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The rate at which the disk of the hard drive turns, in revolutions per minute. This is one determinant of the rate at which data can be read from or written to the disk.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spindle Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all computer hardware. These are the physical elements that create a computer system. Hardware includes the peripherals, the circuits, and other system units.
Software that converts HTML content and formatting information (expressed in CSS or XSL, for example) and renders the content on a display device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: HTML Layout Engine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an HTML Layout Engine to a browser that includes the layout engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Browsers
Internet Protocol
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This duplicates the existing type internet.protocol. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:internet.protocol]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that consists of a set of keys that allow data to be entered into another electronics product.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Keyboard

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates the given computer keyboard to the layout of the keyboard, e.g. QWERTY, AZERTY, and DVORAK.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Keyboard Layout

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A personal computer whose components are all incorporated into a single, light-weight, and portable unit.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Laptop Computer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing companies that manufacture computers and associated hardware.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Manufacturer/Brand

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer manufacturer to a line of computers that the company produces.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Lines

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a computer manufacturer to a model of computers that the company produces.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Models

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all computer memory. Computer memory is made up of the physical devices that store the programs or data for instances of mso:computer.computer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Memory

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Indicates whether or not the given computer memory is buffered, i.e. contains a buffer to reduce the electrical load on the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Buffered Memory

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates the given computer memory to a specification of the way in which data is stored in the memory device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Memory Format

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates the given computer memory to specifications of memory failure tests built into the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Memory Integrity Tests

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Indicates whether or not the given computer memory is registered, i.e. contains a a component to delay the transfer of data by one clock cycle.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Registered Memory

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The amount of data, in Bytes, that can be stored in the computer memory.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Memory Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an instance of computer.memory to the speed in megahertz with which stored data can be transferred to and from the memory.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Memory Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A small, flat, non-volatile, and reprogrammable electronic data storage device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Memory Card

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a given instance of a memory card to information about the speed class of the memory card.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Memory Card Speed Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type that stores information the speed class of a given memory card, viz. the minimum writing performance of the memory card.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Memory Card Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an instance of computer.memory_card_speed to a string specifying the standard for the speed class, e.g. "UHS".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Memory Card Speed Standard

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating computer.memory_speed_card to a decimal number indicating one of the six speed classes, viz. 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, and 10.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Memory Speed Card Value

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all mobile devices. These devices are computing devices that are relatively easy to carry. Subclasses of this collection include smartphones, handheld gaming devices, tablets, and laptops.
Property relating an mso:computer.mobile_device to the description of its front camera.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Front Camera

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.mobile_device to the description of its rear camera.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rear Camera

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.mobile_device to the description of the sound or audio features.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sound

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An abbreviation of modulator-demodulator, a modem enables electronic signals of one type of device to be converted to signals of another type of device, so that they can, for example, be transmitted and received.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Modem

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A circuit board containing the principal components of a computer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Motherboard

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The maximum frequency at which data can be transferred across the main communication system of the motherboard in megahertz, e.g. 92 MHz or 806 MHz.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Motherboard Bus Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer motherboard to processors that are not included with the motherboard but can be used with it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Motherboard Compatible Processors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A specification of the types of sockets that are used on the motherboard to link it to included or compatible processors.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Processor Sockets

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Processors that are components of the given motherboard.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Motherboard Processors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A handheld device that allows data to be entered into another electronics device by moving and clicking on it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Mouse

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that transfers data packets between computer networks.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Network Router

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The software on a computer that controls basic functions like file management and interaction with peripherals.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Operating System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a family of operating systems to one of the operating systems in the family.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Includes OS Versions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an operating system to a person, company or organization that had a role in creating the operating system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Operating System Developer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an operating system to the family of operating systems that it is a part of.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Parent OS

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an operating system to a computer processor that is capable of running the operating system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Supported Architectures

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all OS developers. Operating systems are the software programs that manage a computer's hardware resources and provide common services for computer programs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Operating System Developer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a company, organization or person to an operating system developed by the company, organization or person.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Operating Systems Developed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A storage device that uses laser light or electromagnetic waves to read/write data to/from an optical disk.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Optical Drive

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.optical_drive to the type of disc labelling technology available on the device, if any.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Disc Labelling
OS Compatibility

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dot Version (high)
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: It is not clear what the intended meaning of this property is. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dot Version (low)
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: It is not clear what the intended meaning of this property is. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Operating System
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use commerce.electronics_product.operating_system to relate a computer to an operating system that can run on the computer. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:commerce.electronics_product.operating_system]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that allows a computer program to be manipulated in some way, e.g. by allowing data to be entered into, rendered by, or stored for the program.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Peripheral

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a peripheral to a computer that is compatible with it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Compatible Computers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: When the peripheral was no longer generally available
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Discontinued

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a specific peripheral to an emulator that emulates the peripheral.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Emulators

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: When the peripheral was first made available to the public
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Introduced

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a peripheral to the company that manufactured it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Manufacturer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a specific peripheral to the class of peripherals that it instantiates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Peripheral Class
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use type.object.type instead. Peripheral classes are represented as subtypes of computer.peripheral. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:type.object.type]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a peripheral to a version of a videogame that is compatible with the peripheral.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Game Versions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a peripheral to a videogame that is compatible with the peripheral.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Games
Computer Peripheral Class
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not needed. Peripheral classes are represented as subtypes of computer.peripheral. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:type.object.type]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Instances
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use type.object.type to link an instance of computer.peripheral to one of its subtypes. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:type.object.type]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: products
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use type.object.type to link an instance of computer.peripheral to one of its subtypes. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:type.object.type]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The component of a computer that executes the instructions of a computer program.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Processor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer processor to the size of in Bytes of the small, fast memory store that is part of the computer processor.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Processor Cache

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a processor to a number that represents how many floating point operations per second that the processor is capable of executing.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: FLOPs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a processor to the number of units in the processor that can read and execute program instructions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Cores

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a processor to the number of processes that can be concurrently executed by the processor.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Threads

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer processor to the family of processors of which it is a part.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Processor Family

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer processor to the company that manufactures the processor.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Manufacturer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer processor to the frequency at which the processor runs, e.g. 92 MHz or 806 MHz.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Processor Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a computer processor to a computer of which it is a component.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Component

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that is the inverse of computer.processor.family. In other words, it relates a computer processor family to a processor that is a member of the family.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Variants

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A company that fabricates computer processors.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Processor Manufacturer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a company that fabricates computer processors to one of their processors.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Processors Manufactured

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A formal language in which computer programs are expressed. A computer programs is a sequenced set of instructions that is executed by a computer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Programming Language

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a programming language to a relatively minor variation or extension of it, e.g. Split-C, Cilk, and C* are dialects of the programming language C.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dialects

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a programming language to the file format used by the language.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: File Format

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a programming language to another programming language in which an interpreter/compiler of the first language is written.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Implementation Language

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a programming language to another language that it impacted, e.g. FORTRAN influenced the C programming language.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Influenced Languages

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a programming language to another language that was impacted by it, e.g. FORTRAN influenced the C programming language.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Influenced by

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a programming language to the date when the programming language was first made available.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Introduced

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a programming language to an operating system for which a compiler/interpreter of the language exists.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Operating System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a relatively minor variation or extension of a programming language to the original programming language, e.g. the programming language C is the parent of Split-C, Cilk, and C*.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Parent Language

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a programming language to a person, company or organization that had a role in creating the programming language.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Developers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a programming language to the fundamental way that the programming language is structured. There are six major programming paradigms: imperative, declarative, functional, object-oriented, logic, and symbolic.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Language Paradigm

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a programming language to a standard with which the language is compliant.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Standard

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a programming language to an enumeration value that specifies the kind of typing, viz. strong or weak, assumed by the language.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Typing
Programming Language Designer
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: There does not seem to be any difference in meaning between computer.programming_language_designer and computer.programming_language_developer. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:computer.programming_language_developer]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A person, company or organization that had a role in creating the programming language.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Programming Language Developer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a programming language developer to a programming language that he, she or it had a role in creating.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Programming Languages Developed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for the fundamental ways that programming languages are structured. There are six major programming paradigms: imperative, declarative, functional, object-oriented, logic, and symbolic.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Programming Language Paradigm

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a programming language paradigm to a programming language that exemplifies the paradigm.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Languages
Protocol Provider
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: The intended meaning of this type is not clear. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A set of digital files that are collaboratively created and maintained and a history of changes to the files.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Repository

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates that the project is no longer actively maintained.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Archived

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the number of users who have bookmarked the repository.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bookmarked Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the number of development branches in the repository.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Branches Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the number of projects that are inactive.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Closed Projects Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the number of commits that have been made to the repository.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Commits Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a repository to a user who is contributing or has contributed to the project.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Contributors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the total number of contributors to the repository.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Contributors Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the name of the default branch of the repository. The default branch is the branch where commits are made unless another branch is specified.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Default Branch

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the number of forks that the repository has. If a respository is not forked, the value of this property should be set to 0.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Forks Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the number of closed issues in the repository
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Issues Closed Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the number of outstanding, unresolved issues in the repository
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Issues Open Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to information about the extent to which various programming languages are used in the repository.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Languages Used

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the last time that a new release was made available as a service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Last Deployed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the number of projects that are active.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Open Projects Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to an owner of the repository. Note that, in technical terms, an owner of a repository has full rights to create, update, and delete content in the repository.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Owner

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates that the repository is viewable beyond the contributors to the project.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Private

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the number of pull requests (requests to have changes committed to the repository) that are currently closed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pull Requests Closed Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the number of pull requests (requests to have changes committed to the repository) that are currently open.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pull Requests Open Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the content of the readme file associated with the project.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Readme

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the number of releases in the repository.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Releases Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the size, in bytes, of all of the files in the repository.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to another repository that is a proper part of the first one.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subrepository

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a repository to the number of users who are subscribed to the repository.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subscribers Count

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Any device, whether mechanical or electronic, that is used to secure a computer or a computer network, e.g. a firewall, an antivirus gateway, a laptop padlock, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Computer Security Device

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all site navigation elements. These are the regions on a web page that allow a user to navigate the site.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Site Navigation Element

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all smartphones. Smartphones are the handheld, mobile phones with additional connectivity and computing ability over feature phones.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Smartphone

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all computer software. Software is the set of machine-readable instructions and associated documentation that direct a computer processor to perform specific actions. Included are applications, code snippets, and scripts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Software

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.software to the mso:computer.code_generation_supported relationship that holds the data about the code generation support the software offers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Code Generation Supported

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.software to the boolean value that indicates if the software supports custom templates for code generation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Custom Templates for Code Generation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.software to the mso:media_common.design_pattern the software supports.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Design Patterns

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an instance of mso:computer.software to the mso:computer.file_format the tool supports exporting.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Export File Formats

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an instance of mso:computer.software to the date that the software was initially made available.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: First Released

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.software to the mso:computer.software that integrates it. This means that the former is available for use in the latter.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: IDE Integration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an instance of mso:computer.software to the mso:computer.file_format that the software supports for importing files.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Import File Formats

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an instance of mso:computer.software to an mso:computer.programming_language whose datatypes are supported by the programming language.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Language-Specific Datatypes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an instance of mso:computer.software to a programming language that was used to create the source code for the software.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Programming Languages Used

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an instance of mso:computer.software to the date that the most recent version of the software was made available.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Latest Release Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an instance of mso:computer.software to the most recent version of the software program. Note that the expected type of this property should eventually be changed to mso:application.software_version.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Latest Version

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property indicating whether or not multiple users can access the given software when it is running on a single computer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Multi-user Support

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a computer program to an operating system that can run the program. In cases where the software is compatible with all versions of an operating system after a particular version, that particular version should be the value of this property and the Boolean property mso:computer.software.os_forward_compatiblity should be set to 1.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Operating System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates that the software is compatible with all versions of the operating system after the one specified with the property mso:computer.software.operating_system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Operating System Forward Compatibility

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an instance of mso:computer.software to a protocol that is used by the software.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Protocols Used
Protocols Provider
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: It is not clear what the intended meaning of this property is. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an instance of mso:computer.software to a company that is responsible for creating, publishing, and/or distributing the software.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Software Company

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an instance of mso:computer.software to a person, company or organization that is responsible for creating the software.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Software Developer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an instance of mso:computer.software to a standard descriptor for the kind of software, e.g. database, web browser, data mining, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Software Genre

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an instance of mso:computer.software to a legal document that specifies how and by whom the software can be used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Software License

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a family of software to a version of the software.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Software Version

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.software entity to its target mso:application.application, which means the software is used in the application.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Target Application
Software Compatibility
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This relationship type is far too complex. All that is needed is the property computer.software.operating_system. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:computer.software.operating_system]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Operating System
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use computer.software.operating_system to relate a computer program to an operating system that can run the program. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:computer.software.operating_system]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: OS Version End
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: It is not clear what this property is intended to mean. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: OS Version Start
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: It is not clear what this property is intended to mean. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Software
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use computer.software.operating_system to relate a computer program to an operating system that can run the program. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:computer.software.operating_system]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all software developers. These are the people or organizations involved in using mso:computer.programming_languages and creating mso:computer.software.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Software Developer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a software developer to a computer program that was created by him, her or it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Software

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for kinds of software, e.g. database, web browser, data mining, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Software Genre

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a software genre to a genre that includes it as a subgenre.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Parent Genre

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a software genre to a computer program that is an instance of the genre.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Software in Genre

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a software genre to another genre that it includes as a subgenre.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subgenres

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A legal document that specifies how and by whom the given software can be used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Software License

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a software license to the family of software licenses that includes it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Version Of

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a family of software licenses to a particular version of the software license.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Versions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A mobile device in which the input and display components are integrated into a single pad.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tablet Computer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A device that reads computer data from and/or writes computer data to magnetic tape.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tape Drive

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The amount of data in bytes that can be stored on the tape drive when it is compressed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tape Drive Compressed Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The specific type of used by the tape drive, e.g. 8mm, DAT, AIT, DLT, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tape Drive Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The amount of data in bytes that can be stored on the tape drive without compression.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Uncompressed Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration type that contains values for the various sorts of typing that are assumed by programming languages.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Typing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value that denotes a programming language where all data types are predefined, and every variable and constant used in a program written with the language is assigned one of these types.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Strong Typing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value that denotes a programming language where not all data types are predefined, and/or not every variable and constant used in a program written with the language is assigned one of these types.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weak Typing

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all UML tools. These are software applications that support UML, which is the standard modeling language used in software engineering.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: UML Tool

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.uml_tool to the mso:common.diagram_types the tool generates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Diagram Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.uml_tool to the boolean value that indicates whether the tool supports model constraints, like forcing single inheritance.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Model Constraint Support

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.uml_tool to the boolean value that indicates whether the tool supports versioning of its created models.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Model Versioning

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.uml_tool to the modeling languages, other than UML, that the tool supports.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Modeling Languages

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.uml_tool to the text description of the tool's OCL support.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Object Constraint Language Support

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.uml_tool to the mso:computer.programming_languages that the tool can parse to generate UML.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Reverse Engineering Languages Supported

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.uml_tool to a boolean representing whether or not the tool supports UML profiles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: UML Profiles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.uml_tool to the mso:application.software_version of UML the tool supports.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: UML Version

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.uml_tool to the versions of XMI, XML Metadata Interchange, that the tool supports for exporting.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: XMI Export

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:computer.uml_tool to the versions of XMI, XML Metadata Interchange, that the tool supports for importing.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: XMI Import

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A chip or board that is added to an electronics product to increase the performance of rendering video.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Video Card

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A subtype of mobile devices covering anything that can be worn, e.g. smart watches and activity trackers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wearable Device

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a wearable device to the color of the band of the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Band Color

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a wearable device to a range of millimeters indicating the smallest and largest wrist that can wear the device.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wrist Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A software application that is capable of retrieving and rendering documents on the World Wide Web.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Web Browser

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a web browser to an HTML layout engine that is included in the web browser.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: HTML Layout Engine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a web browser to an independent computer program that supplements the functionality of the web browser.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Web Browser Extension

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An independent computer program that supplements the functionality of a web browser.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Web Browser Extension

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a web browser extension to a web browser that it is capable of extending.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Works on Web Browser

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all web page ad blocks. These are the areas of advertising for a web page.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ad Block

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all web page elements. These are the discrete regions of the web page, like a table, image, header, or footer. These regions may or may not have associated HTML tags to denote the space in the DOM.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Web Page Element

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all web page footers. These are the areas at the bottom of a webpage that contain technical information for the page, including the page author, last modification date, and copyright information.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Footer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all web page headers. Headers are the rectangular areas running across the top of the web page. Usually these spaces provide navigation and branding for the website.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Header

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all sidebars. Sidebars are the web page elements that contain information to the side of the main window or canvas of an application.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sidebar

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all tables on web pages. These are the regions on a web page that arrange data in columns and rows.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Table

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains any service that allows computing devices to connect wirelessly to the Internet.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wifi Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a wifi service to a description of the sort of encryption used for packets transmitted over the service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Encryption

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a wifi service to the location(s) where the service can be accessed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a wifi service to the password needed to access the service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Password

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a wifi service to the agent(s) that provide the service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Provider

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a wifi service with the unique SSID for the service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Service Set Identifier

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Parameters of the Microsoft Windows operating systems that can be viewed and/or manipulated by users of the software.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Windows Setting

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether the Windows setting is accessible through the Control Panel, the dashboard of Windows operating systems.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Control Panel

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A network router that also has the function of allowing wireless devices to connect to a wired computer network.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wireless Router
